I agree, it is a dumb question. Not because of the question itself; equipment is the deciding factor in whether or not you die in EQ, along with not being retarded.

Matching armor? Ughh, if you REALLY care, just dye. As for good armor...what race? It really doesn't matter, just camp the bazaar. Look for hp/ac stuff and you'll be fine.

Totemic and similar did my shaman fine at 34-40ish; perhaps it's your combat methods? Where do you hunt? For one thing, if there's no enchanter in the group, pull 2-4 mobs, root all of them but one. Slow that one, and get teh group to /assist, then slow/root/dot the others. Exp is amazing, and if you're not main healer, it shouldn't be too hard on your mana base.

You could always solo the mobs at Sol A. That's where I hunted, the exp was great and easy. Just don't go too far in until 39 (when you should be able to wipe the entire place with maybe one partner).

